Morphological variability. In adult specimens, the body length, length of postabdomen, postabdominal claws, swimming antennae, length of tl I and of its basal segment were the most variable structures (
Table 1
). The same was true for the number of antennal setae, denticles of postabdominal claws, and number of setae in thoracic limbs, which were most variable in the proximal segments of tl II–tl V and in distal segments of tl I and tl II (
Table 2
).
